A man from Hrob "pierced" his girlfriend from Kostomlaty
The man from Hradec Králové unintentionally helped the police officers to secure his nationwide wanted girlfriend from Kostomlaty nad Labem, who had a warrant for her arrest.
He summoned her himself.
However, he did so in a roundabout way.
First, he approached a passer-by and made up a story that he had been robbed.
Officers responding to the 911 call arrived on scene and were stunned when the alleged "victim" told them he made the whole thing up to get officers to come to the scene.
In fact, he only wanted to ask the officers how to file a report with the Czech Police.
After checking the identity of the man and his companion, the officers discovered that the woman was on the list of wanted persons, in a nationwide search, and an arrest warrant had been issued for her.
The case is therefore being handled by the Czech police.
