According to the law, COVID-19 is on the list of infectious diseases.
That is, in the same group as HIV, the plague, yellow fever, or typhus.
§ 152 Dissemination of a Contagious Human Disease
(1) Any person who knowingly causes or increases the risk of the introduction or spread of an infectious disease in humans shall be punished by imprisonment for six months to three years, a ban on activities or the forfeiture of a thing.
(2) The offender shall be sentenced to a term of imprisonment of two to eight years.
c) commits a breach of an important duty arising from his employment, profession, position or function or imposed on him by law, or
d) causing serious bodily injury.
(3) The offender shall be punished by imprisonment for a term of three to ten years, if, by the act provided for in paragraph 1, he has caused serious bodily harm to at least two persons or death.
(4) A sentence of imprisonment for a term of five to twelve years will be imposed on the perpetrator if he has caused the death of at least two persons by the act referred to in paragraph 1.
