According to Ziobro, the European Commission would be acting unlawfully if it used its new powers to withhold payments to Poland due to the rule-of-law dispute.
The Commission has already delayed approval of Poland's plan to tap 36 billion euros from the EU's recovery fund for economies hit by the COVID-19 pandemic.
And it is under pressure from the European Parliament to go further and use a mechanism to withdraw EU funds from countries that violate the rule of law.
"Poland should respond to this blackmail by the EU with a veto in all matters requiring unanimity," said Ziobro, head of the small Solidarity Poland party, without whose votes the current government would lose its narrow majority in the Sejm.
