British woman Vicki Holland tortured Milly the capuchin monkey
Shocking footage shows the moment a terrified monkey cowered in a toilet bowl before its heartless owner flushed it away and laughed.
Holland also fed the monkey hot dogs, kebabs and hamburgers, regardless of her actual nutritional needs.
Gwent Magistrates' Court has now banned her from keeping animals for life, The Sun reports.
The primate rehabilitation experts looking after Milly after her ordeal have said they have never seen a monkey so terrified.
Milly spent almost two years in rehabilitation with staff at Monkey World in Dorset and is now happily playing with another rescued monkey called Moon.
The mother-of-four admitted two charges of causing unnecessary suffering to a protected animal.
She was given a 12-week prison sentence, suspended for 12 months, at Gwent Magistrates' Court.
Holland was also sentenced to 120 hours of unpaid work, received a lifetime ban from keeping animals, and must pay court costs of approximately 12,000 Czech crowns.
Steph Sawyer, head of the Small Monkeys team that rehabilitated the abused animal, said: "Milly is doing well but her rehabilitation will continue."
It took Milly a while to get used to people again.
She crouched and hid from anyone she encountered and any loud noise or sudden movement caused her to scream.
The monkey refused to eat for a long time.
Even now that she's settled and happy with her mate, the sight of new people can still send her into a panic.
The mental scars from the abuse will stay with her forever, says Sawyer.
Milly's abuse came to light after police in Gwent discovered the horrifying footage on her phone following a drugs raid at her home.
In the footage, Milly can be heard swearing.
In another video, Ms. Holland is heard offering the monkey cocaine and saying, "You want some coke?"
So, lick my fingers.
In May she and her partner Russell Cox (43) admitted possession of cocaine with intent to supply.
Her home was found to contain cocaine worth £1,600 (around 50,000 Czech crowns) hidden in Kinder eggs.
Cox was jailed for 30 months and Holland received a 20-month suspended sentence.
