New timetables come into force in Prague on Sunday, affecting mainly suburban services
Passengers in Prague's integrated transport system (PID) can look forward to a number of changes from Sunday, mainly affecting suburban services.
New lines have been created, some have changed their routes, and others have disappeared.
Mladoboleslavsko is now joining the integrated system.
From Sunday, fast trains from České Budějovice will stop at the Zahradní Město station in the capital.
In suburban rail transport, S7 trains will run, which pass through Prague's main station on the route from Beroun to Český Brod.
The recently opened station of Prague-Zahradní Město will now be served by the R17 express train from České Budějovice and Benešov.
The PID will now be extended to other areas.
In addition, the buses will go as far as Světlá nad Sázavou, Blatná u Jesenice, Staré Splavy and Turnov.
Buses in the Mladá Boleslav region will be included, including lines with transfers to the Liberec and Hradec Králové regions.
During the integration, 77 lines will be scrapped, 37 new lines will be introduced and the operation of 12 existing lines will be changed.
A new bus line 405 will depart from Prague's Zličín. It will go all the way to Žatec.
A new direct connection between Prague and Kralovice near Rakovník has also been created, replacing the cancelled S53 train line.
The Prague-Rakovník connection will be strengthened in the morning rush hour and at the weekend, when a new express line number 404 will run.
New to the PID system are lines 400 and 410, which go to the Liberec region.
They leave from the Střížkov metro station, not from the Nádraží Holešovice station.
The 400 spine line runs through Mělník, Dubá and Česká Lípa to Nový Bor, and selected services continue to Rumburk or Cvikov.
The supplementary line 410 goes via Mělník and Dubá to Doksy, Mimoň and Jablonné v Podještědí.
In contrast, the operation of dozens of local routes in the Central Bohemian region has been cancelled or restricted, including to Mochov, Dobříš or Rožmitál pod Třemšínem.
All trains leaving Prague at 02:30 have been cancelled.
Due to the modernisation of the railway, there will be long-term restrictions on the tracks from Prague to Beroun, Prague to Lysá nad Labem, and in the vicinity of Kolín.
There will also be changes for passengers at other locations.
Buses are replacing some cancelled railway lines or the section of line 420 from Dobříš with connections from Prague, where it is possible to use PID tickets all the way to Milevsko.
The routes of lines 540 to 543 in Nymburk have been changed, and the routes of some buses on the border of the Central Bohemian Region and Hořovicko in the Plzeň Region have been adjusted.
