A record-breaking drought in the Czech Republic.
It is necessary to change agricultural subsidies, the landscape is not just a food factory, says the journalist.
The Czech Republic is experiencing the worst drought in years.
According to scientists, there is less water in mountainous and sub-mountainous areas, and places that have not yet experienced a water shortage are also recording less rainfall.
