Agent Tesla is terrorising pre-Christmas Czechia.
While data in October indicated a slight decrease in attack campaigns, last month saw a significant uptick as the end of the year approached.
We observed a major Agent Tesla campaign on November 18.
The attacks are targeted at the Czech Republic.
For now, the attackers' strategy remains the same.
The infected attachment in the email is designed to catch the user's attention with a name that refers to payments and financial transactions.
While last month's dangerous attachment had the word "invoice" in the name, this time it was marked as Copy of receipt for 11,2021...exe," said Martin Jirkal from Eset.
The spyware includes features that scan web browsers and other programs, such as Microsoft Outlook, Mozilla Thunderbird, and Yandex email clients.
The malicious code actively searches for saved login details, which it then sends to the attackers.
The last major campaign in the Czech Republic took place at the end of August and the beginning of September, and with the approaching holidays and the end of the year, the activity of the attackers is growing again.
In November, the spyware Formbook remained active.
In contrast to Agent Tesla, in this case the attackers are not specifically targeting the Czech Republic, and the security experts detected more of a global campaign in November.
Compared to Formbook's October data, it weakened slightly in November, but still accounts for nearly a fifth of all detections.
The attacks were continuous throughout the month with increased activity on the 3rd, 10th, and 15th of November.
The formbook most commonly contained an attachment with the .exe extension named REQUEST FOR SPECIFICATION.
However, the term receipt continues to be used.
The attachment in Czech is then much more dangerous for the Czech user.
Security analysts have observed a significant decline and a slowdown in the activity of the Fareit programme, which was responsible for 1.6 per cent of attacks and has not carried out a major attack campaign in the Czech Republic for several months.
